   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF THE MINOR PROPHETS MESSAGE TWENTY ON OBADIAH JEHOVAH S DEALING WITH ESAU</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>JACOB S VICTORY FOR THE KINGDOM OF JEHOVAH Scripture Reading: Obad.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>1-21</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In this message we will consider the prophecy of Obadiah.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>I. THE INTRODUCTORY WORD A. The Meaning of the Name Obadiah</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In Hebrew the name Obadiah means the servant of Jehovah.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>B. The Time of Obadiah s Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The time of Obadiah s ministry was about 880 or 587 B.C. It is hard to determine which date is correct.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>C. The Object of His Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The object of Obadiah s ministry was the southern kingdom of Judah.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>D. The Place of His Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The place of Obadiah s ministry also was the southern kingdom of Judah.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>E. The Subject</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The subject of the book of Obadiah is Jehovah s dealing with Esau and Jacob s victory for the kingdom of Jehovah, which is the manifestation of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>F. The Central Thought</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The central thought of Obadiah is that Jehovah s dealing with Esau issues in Jacob s victory and possession for the kingdom of God in the age of restoration.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>G. The Sections</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The book of Obadiah has five sections: the introductory word v. 1a ; Jehovah s dealings with Edom vv.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>1b-9 ; the evils of Edom vv.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>10-14 ; the day of Jehovah upon all the nations vv.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>15-16 ; and the issue of Jehovah s dealing vv.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>17-21 .</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>JEHOVAH S DEALINGS WITH EDOM</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Verses 1b through 9 are concerned with Jehovah s dealings with Edom.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Whereas Esau is the name of a person, the twin brother of Jacob, Edom is the name of a country.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>A. Stirring Up the Nations</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>to Rise Up against It for Battle</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Jehovah dealt with Edom by stirring up the nations to rise up against it for battle v. 1b .</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>B. Having Made Edom Small among the Nations</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>God purposely dealt with Edom by making him small among the nations and very much despised v. 2 . As a result, Edom was a lowly nation.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>C. Bringing Edom Down from Its Dwelling</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>in the Lofty Clefts of the Rock to the Ground</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Because of its arrogance Jehovah will bring Edom from its dwelling in the lofty clefts of the rock to the ground vv.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>3-4 .</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The people of Edom were proud of their lofty dwelling and thought that they were higher and more lofty than others.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>D. Edom s Being Plundered</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>by the Thieves and Spoilers</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Jehovah s dealing with Edom included their being plundered by the thieves and spoilers vv.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>5-6 .</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Although they lived in the lofty places, the thieves and spoilers still visited them.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>E. Edom s Being Deceived by Its Confederacy</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Edom was also deceived by its confederacy v. 7 . Some nations formed a confederacy with Edom, but eventually they were unfaithful to Edom.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>F. Destroying Its Wise Men,</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Dismaying Its Mighty Men, and</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Cutting Off Each One from the Mountain of Esau</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Jehovah dealt with Edom further by destroying its wise men, dismaying its mighty men, and cutting off each one from the mountain of Esau vv.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>8-9 .</S>
   </TEXT>
